title: "Agamians Magazine" Tee
body_html:
"Agamians Magazine" Tee talks about the people who used to spend their summer in a beach in Alexandria, Egypt called El Agami. In the 1950s, the city was a compound for the elite class of Egypt. The magazine shares the vibes back in the 60s with some comic phrases and of course including "Mawlah" fashion dream week that might have been happened back then.

 

Washing Instructions:

1- Machine wash in old water 30 degrees inside out to avoid any shrinking

2- Do not bleach

3- Do not iron the printed part
